analysis: The documents primarily focus on establishing and modifying wildlife refuges and breeding grounds, mainly for migratory birds, across various states including Montana, Iowa, Washington, Minnesota, North Dakota, and New Mexico. These refuges are created by withdrawing public lands from various forms of appropriation and reserving them for the use of either the Department of the Interior or the Department of Agriculture. The documents also outline restrictions on activities like hunting, trapping, and disturbing wildlife within these areas. Several orders modify existing refuges or correct errors in land descriptions. The purpose is to conserve and develop natural wildlife resources.
title: Establishment and Modification of Wildlife Refuges
